---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Ulisses Balbino — filmmaker, director, founder of Pichorra Filmes. Writing about AI from inside the production chain."
>
  <section class="container" style="padding: 5rem 1.25rem 3rem;">
    <h1 class="title">About</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="prose">
    <p>
      I'm Ulisses Balbino. I've been directing commercial work since 2012 and
      co-founded Pichorra Filmes in São Paulo with Lisandra Barros. Over the last
      14 years I've worked on projects across Disney, Starbucks, Yamaha, Carrefour,
      Benefit, Nestlé, and others — composer, actor, editor, writer, director.
      Every seat on a set, at some point.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Open Your AIs</strong> is where I write about AI from inside the
      production chain. No hype, no fear-mongering, no "everything is about to change."
      Just what I actually test, what actually works, and what actually breaks.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you want the short version of my stance: AI is a tool. It's cheap, fast,
      and genuinely useful for the mechanical parts of creative work. It's still
      terrible at taste, and taste is the only thing that ever mattered.
    </p>
    <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
    <p>
      Every AI launch is followed by weeks of press releases pretending the tool
      is magic and weeks of think-pieces pretending it's the apocalypse. Neither
      version helps a working creator decide what to actually use on Monday. This
      site is my attempt at the third version — a director's field notes.
    </p>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Write to me via the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>, or find me on
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ulissesbalbino/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
      and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/ulissesbalbino/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
